{"title_page": "100% Footy", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{notability|sports|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = 100% Footy\n| image                    = \n| image_size               = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| show_name_2              = \n| genre                    = Sport\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = \n| developer                = \n| writer                   = \n| director                 = \n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = [[Erin Molan]]\n| starring                 = [[Peter Sterling (rugby league commentator)|Peter Sterling]]<br />[[Brad Fittler]]<br />[[Allana Ferguson]]\n| judges                   = \n| voices                   = <!-- Organized by broadcast credit order, with new main cast added to the end of the list -->\n| narrated                 = \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = [[Australia]]\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 24\n| num_episodes             = 600+\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = Matt Callander<br />Sean Burke\n| producer                 = \n| editor                   = \n| location                 = [[TCN-9]] [[Willoughby, New South Wales]]\n| cinematography           = \n| camera                   = \n| runtime                  = 120 minutes <small>(inc. adverts)</small>\n| company                  = \n| distributor              = \n| channel                  = [[Nine Network]]\n| picture_format           = [[576i]] ([[Standard-definition television|SDTV]])<br />[[1080i]] ([[high-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = Stereo\n| release                  = <!-- Use 'y' / 'Y' / 'yes' / 'Yes' -->\n| first_run                =\n| first_aired              = 2018\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = \n| followed_by              = \n| related                  = \n| website                  = http://www.9jumpin.com.au/show/nrlsundayfootyshow/\n| website_title            = \n| production_website       = \n| production_website_title = \n}}\n\n'''''100% Footy''''' is an [[Australia]]n sports talk show that deals with issues in the [[National Rugby League|NRL]]. Hosted by sports presenter James Bracey.<ref>https://tvtonight.com.au/2018/04/james-bracey-to-step-in-as-host-of-nrl-footy-show.html</ref> it airs on the [[Nine Network]], first screening in 2018, in a late night timeslot on Monday nights.<ref>https://www.nineentertainmentco.com.au/brand-100-footy</ref>\n\nThe show usually features a round up of the week's football matches, including highlights from the weekend and previews of upcoming matches. It also includes discussion of news in rugby league, plus player and coaching interviews.<ref>https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/tv-and-radio/now-it-s-axed-the-footy-show-here-s-what-nine-should-do-next-20181002-p507cx.html</ref>\n\n==Hosts==\n===Presenters===\n* [[James Bracey]]\n* [[Phil Gould (rugby league)|Phil Gould]] \n* [[Paul Gallen]]\n* [[Ruan Sims]]\n* [[Neil Breen]]\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Television|Australia|Sports}}\n* \n* [[List of Australian television series]]\n* [[The Sunday Footy Show (rugby league)]]\n* [[The Sunday Roast]]\n* [[Boots 'N' All#International Syndication]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{NRL}}\n{{Nine Network programming}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:100 Footy}}\n[[Category:Nine's Wide World of Sport]]\n[[Category:2018 Australian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2000s Australian television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Australian television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Australian sports television series]]\n[[Category:Rugby league television programmes]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{notability|sports|date=June 2019}}\n{{Info