         = http://www.9jumpin.com.au/show/nrlsundayfootyshow/\n| website_title            = \n| production_website       = \n| production_website_title = \n}}\n\n'''''100% Footy''''' is an [[Australia]]n sports talk show that deals with issues in the [[National Rugby League|NRL]]. Hosted by sports presenter James Bracey.<ref>https://tvtonight.com.au/2018/04/james-bracey-to-step-in-as-host-of-nrl-footy-show.html</ref> it airs on the [[Nine Network]], first screening in 2018, in a late night timeslot on Monday nights.<ref>https://www.nineentertainmentco.com.au/brand-100-footy</ref>\n\nThe show usually features a round up of the week's football matches, including highlights from the weekend and previews of upcoming matches. It also includes discussion of news in rugby league, plus player and coaching interviews.<ref>https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/tv-and-radio/now-it-s-axed-the-footy-show-here-s-what-nine-should-do-next-20181002-p507cx.html</ref>\n\n==Hosts==\n===Presenters===\n* [[James Bracey]]\n* [[Phil Gould]] \n* [[Paul Gallen]]\n* [[Ruan Sims]]\n* [[Neil Breen]]\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Television|Australia|Sports}}\n* \n* [[List of Australian television series]]\n* [[The Sunday Footy Show (rugby league)]]\n* [[The Sunday Roast]]\n* [[Boots 'N' All#International Syndication]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{NRL}}\n{{Nine Network programming}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:100 Footy}}\n[[Category:Nine's Wide World of Sport]]\n[[Category:2018 Australian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2000s Australian television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Australian television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Australian sports television series]]\n[[Category:Rugby league television programmes]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toPhilip Gould (disambiguation)(link changed toPhil Gould (rugby league)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/100%25_Footy"}
{"title_page": "2019 All Stars match", "text_new": "{{Infobox rugby league football match (quarters)|year=2019|title=All Stars match|image=|imagesize=150px|alt=|home=Indigenous All Stars|away=M\u0101ori All Stars|home_abbr=IND|away_abbr=MAO|home_quarter1=10|home_quarter2=10|home_quarter3=4|home_quarter4=10|home_total=34|away_quarter1=6|away_quarter2=4|away_quarter3=4|away_quarter4=0|away_total=14|date=15 February 2019|stadium=[[Melbourne Rectangular Stadium|AAMI Park]]|location=[[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]|MoM_title=[[Preston Campbell]] Medal|MoM=[[Tyrone Roberts]]|anthem_title=|anthem=|referee=Grant Atkins|referee2=Gavin Badger|attendance=18,802|network=|commentators=Mat Thompson|commentators2=[[Phil Gould (rugby league)|Phil Gould]]|commentators3=[[Andrew Johns]]|commentators4=|tournaments=[[All Stars match]]|last=[[2017 All Stars match|2017]]|next=[[2020 All Stars match|2020]]}}The '''2019 All Stars match''' was the eighth annual representative exhibition [[All Stars match]] of [[Rugby league in Australia|Australian rugby league]]. The match was played between the [[Indigenous All Stars (rugby league)|Indigenous All Stars]] and the [[New Zealand M\u0101ori rugby league team|M\u0101ori All Stars]] and for the first time, the match was played in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]'s [[Melbourne Rectangular Stadium|AAMI Park]]. The match was held on the 15 February 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportingnews.com/au/league/news/nrl-announce-new-all-stars-concept-indigenous-new-zealand-maori-2019-pre-season-josh-addo-carr-jesse-bromwich/1perz3wa9qkp01rbyp50rv50xo|title=NRL announce new All-Stars concept to kick-off 2019 NRL season|website=www.sportingnews.com|language=en-AU|access-date=2018-11-04}}</ref>\n\n== Teams ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin: 1em auto 1em auto\"\n!  align=\"centre\" style=\"width:170px; border:3px solid gold; background:black; color:white\"|INDIGENOUS<br>ALL STARS\n! align=\"center\" width=\"100\" style=\"backgr