ll-stars/|website=NRL.com|date=2 February 2019}}</ref><br/>\n<sup>3</sup> - [[Jordan McLean]] was originally selected to play but withdrew. [[James Tamou]] was moved from the bench to Prop and McLean was replaced by [[Kenny Bromwich]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bromwich to replace McLean in M\u0101ori All Stars|url=https://www.nrl.com/news/2019/02/04/jordan-mclean-out-of-maori-all-stars-kenny-bromwich-called-in/|website=NRL.com|date=4 February 2019}}</ref><br/>\n<sup>4</sup> - [[Tyrell Fuimaono]] was originally selected to play but withdrew. He was replaced by [[Craig Garvey]].\n\n== Result ==\n{{rugbyleaguebox\n|bg         = #f1f5fc\n|date       = 15 February 2019\n|time       = 8:20pm (AEDT)\n|team1      = [[Indigenous All Stars (rugby league)|Indigenous All Stars]] [[File:Australian Aboriginal Flag.svg|23px]]\n|score      = 34 &ndash; 14\n|report     = <ref>{{cite news|title=Addo-Carr stars as Indigenous All Stars beat M\u0101ori All Stars|url=https://www.nrl.com/news/2019/02/15/addo-carr-stars-as-indigenous-all-stars-beat-maori-all-stars/|website=NRL.com|date=15 February 2019}}</ref><br>1st: 10 - 6<br/>2nd: 10 - 4<br/>3rd: 4 - 4<br/>4th: 10 - 0\n|team2      = {{flagicon|New Zealand M\u0101ori}} [[New Zealand M\u0101ori rugby league team|M\u0101ori All Stars]]\n|points1    = '''Tries:'''<br>[[Josh Addo-Carr]] (11', 14') '''2'''<br>[[Bevan French]] (33') '''1'''<br>[[Blake Ferguson]] (39') '''1'''<br>[[David Fifita (rugby league, born 2000)|David Fifita]] (45') '''1'''<br>[[Cody Walker (rugby league)|Cody Walker]] (64') '''1'''<br>[[Josh Kerr (rugby league)|Josh Kerr]] (73') '''1'''<br/>'''Goals:'''<br>[[Latrell Mitchell]] '''3/7'''<br/>(15', 40', 75')<br/>'''Field Goals:'''<br>[[Tyrone Roberts]] '''0/1'''\n|points2    = '''Tries:'''<br>[[Dane Gagai]] (3', 28') '''2'''<br>[[Esan Marsters]] (51') '''1'''<br/>'''Goals:'''<br>[[Jordan Kahu]] '''1/2'''<br/>(4')<br/>[[Esan Marsters]] '''0/1'''\n|stadium    = [[Melbourne Rectangular Stadium|AAMI Park]]\n|referee    = Grant 